The propaganda published by this route costs virtually nothing compared to the usual recruitment advertising on television, to be communicated to BBC Gordon Mackenzie, a defence consultant. On the other hand, it inevitably carries a political message as it justifies in a special form the well-founded military operations decided by the government.
The Americans played a game
