Congress approves the transposition of Mifid, which entered into force on 1 November.
In parallel with its parliamentary formality, which ended today with the vote of Congress on amendments incorporated into the bill in the Senate, the Government has submitted to a public hearing the regulation that will develop the new law, with the objective of its entry into force before the end of the year.
The representatives of the various groups agreed to highlight the efforts of Members of Parliament and senators to negotiate and consent to the best regulation able to ensure investor protection and to regulate in detail the organization's activity for the effective functioning of the markets.
Mifid, which amends the Securities Market Act, implies the modernisation of financial markets, at the time it strengthens investor protection, improves the powers of the National Securities Market Commission (NCMV) and promotes cooperation among the various EU leaders.
The new regulations will enable financial consultation services to be provided both for specialized social reasons and for natural or legal persons and create a new type of financial services (ESIS), financial consulting companies (AFI), which merge with securities companies, securities agencies and portfolio managers.
In addition, it increases the number of systems for the execution of operations on financial instruments, so that it is possible to add to regulated secondary markets multilateral trading systems and international order systems, which compete with current stock exchange managers.
